div.p: TCP packets have to travel through numerous hops to get from a laptop all the way to a server. A server can be physically located in another country or another continent. To get to the server TCP packets have to navigate through various so-called "Autonomous Systems" with a help of Border Gateway Protocol. Click BGP to get more information

div.p: An ARP lookup is needed in order to identify the MAC address of the machine that has a specific IP address. If ARP table does not have an entry for an IP address in question, it will perform ARP lookup
